title: Thema 1 Nieuw
description: In dit eerste thema maken de leerlingen kennis met de Engelse taal. We hebben een opdrachtje voor de vaardigheden lezen, spreken, kijken/luisteren en lezen.

items.content:
Welcome to the English Wikiwijs page!

Here you're going to find all the documents you need for this theme. We're going to do our first tasks together. You can click on the four Parts on the left to see which assignments we're going to do. There's going to be a Reading, Speaking, Listening/Watching and Writing exercise.

In the first Theme, we're just going to get to know each other and work in English. In the next Themes, you're going to learn more grammar and words and work on your skills.

Have fun!

Your teachers.

In this section, you can find the first Vocabulary Task we're going to do together. You're going to play a game that might seem familiar! (bekend voorkomen).

Task 1.

Play the Game of the Goose in a group. While you're playing, write down the answers (antwoorden) you and your group mates give. Make sure you try to answer the game questions in English. If you don't know a word, look it up in an online dictionary (woordenboek) or ask your expert.

You can find the game displayed (weergegeven, afgebeeld) on the digiboard or you can open the PDF-document to see what the game looks like. Of course you will receive (krijgen) the game on paper so you can play.

Find a small object to use as your pawn (pion) and you can use an online dice (dobbelsteen) to roll!

Have fun!

items.title: Three Little Pigs - Revolting Rhymes by Roald Dahl
Listening and Watching Task - Three Little Pigs

items.content:
In this section you can find the first Listening and Watching Task we're going to do together. First, we're going to watch the 'Three Little Pigs' clip from the Revolting Rhymes by Roald Dahl together and then we're going to answer the questions.

Tip: read the questions before you start watching, so you know what to look for!

Task 1.

Read the questions about the video. You can read the questions below or you can open the PDF document to see which assignments we're going to do. Then watch the Roald Dahl clip via the link to YouTube. Write your answers in a Google document.

If the questions are in English, you answer in English. If the questions are in Dutch, you can answer in English or Dutch.

Questions

  1. Hoeveel biggetjes zitten er in het verhaaltje van Roald Dahl?

  2. Waar is het huisje van het eerste biggetje van gemaakt?

  3. Waar is het huis van het derde biggetje van gemaakt?

  4. Lukt het de wolf om het huisje van het derde biggetje om te blazen?

  5. Welke slimme truc haalt de wolf uit om het derde biggetje toch op te kunnen eten?

  6. Wat draagt Little Red Riding Hood (Roodkapje) op het einde van het filmpje?

  7. Waar is de tas van gemaakt die Little Red Riding Hood (Roodkapje) op het einde van het verhaaltje bij zich heeft?

In this section you can find the first Speaking Task we're going to do together. You are going to interview a classmate. Write down the answers (antwoorden) your classmate gives you. Make sure you try to ask your questions in English! When you're done, swap (wisselen/omdraaien) roles.

Task 1.

You can find the interview questions below or you can open the PDF document to see which assignments we're going to do. Find a classmate and do the interview. When you are done, swap roles.

'The Interview'

What's your name?

___________________________________________________________________

How old are you?

___________________________________________________________________

Do you have brothers or sisters? What are their names?

___________________________________________________________________

What are your hobbies?

___________________________________________________________________

Have you been on holiday? Where have you been on holiday?

___________________________________________________________________

What is your favourite colour?

___________________________________________________________________

What is your favourite food?

___________________________________________________________________

My favourite subject (schoolvak) at school is …

___________________________________________________________________

The strangest thing (raarste gebeurtenis) that has ever happened to me is …

___________________________________________________________________

___________________________________________________________________

The best day of my life was when …

___________________________________________________________________

___________________________________________________________________

In this section, you can find the first Reading Task we're going to do together. First, read the text about Tracey. She has her first day at a new school (just like you guys). After reading the text we're going to answer the questions.

Tip: you can read the questions before reading the text to know what to look for!

Task 1.

Read the questions about the text. Then read the text completely. You can work on the exercises below or open the PDF document to see which assignments we're going to do. Write down the answers to the questions in your English Google Doc.

If you don't know a word, look it up in an online dictionary or ask your expert.

'The New School'

Tracey is starting a new school today. She is very sad. She is very scared. "I don't want to go to school today," Tracey tells her dad. "I understand, sweetheart," Dad says. "Starting a new school can be very scary."

Tracey has moved to a new town. She has moved to a new house. She is starting a new school today. She has done all of this in a week!

"I feel sick," Tracey says. "My stomach hurts. I can't eat breakfast."
"I think that is because you are nervous," Dad says. He pets Tracey's hair. He gives her a little hug.

"Try drinking just a little juice. Then I will walk you to school." Tracey and her dad walk to school. Tracey thinks about many things.

Will I make friends? Will I like my teacher? What if I don't know the answer to a question? Will kids laugh at me? What if no one likes me?

"We're here," says Dad. Tracey looks up at the big building. Her other school was small. Tracey wishes she could run away. She knows she can't. She takes a deep breath. She walks up the steps to school. She walks into her third-grade classroom.

"That must be Tracey," she hears a boy say. "Hello, Tracey!" "Welcome, Tracey!" "Let me show you around."

Everyone seems kind. Tracey feels a little better. But she is still not happy. She is still a little scared. She cannot eat her lunch. Dad picks Tracey up after school.

"How was your day?" he asks. "Okay," she says. "It will get better," Dad says. "Big changes are hard." "I know," says Tracey.

She reaches for her dad's hand to hold as they walk home.

Questions

1) Why is Tracey sad and scared?
A. She is moving to a new house today.
B. She is moving to a new town today.
C. She is starting a new school today.
D. She is walking to school alone today.

2) What has Tracey done during the week?
I. made a new friend
II. moved to a new town
III. moved to a new house

A. I only
B. I and II
C. II and III
D. I, II, and III

3) What grade is Tracey in?
A. second grade
B. third grade
C. fourth grade
D. fifth grade

4) Why can't Tracey eat breakfast?
I. She is nervous.
II. Her stomach hurts.
III. She is late for school.

A. I only
B. I and II
C. II and III
D. I, II, and III

5) Why does Tracey's dad think she feels sick?
A. because she is sleepy
B. because she is nervous
C. because she has a cold
D. because she ate too much

6) As used at the beginning of the story, what does nervous mean?
A. to be happy
B. to be hungry
C. to be mad
D. to be scared

7) What does Dad tell Tracey to do before school?
A. stop crying
B. get her bag
C. drink some juice
D. put on her shoes

8) How do Tracey and Dad get to school?
A. They drive.
B. They walk.
C. They run.
D. They take the bus.

9) What does Tracey think about most as she walks?
A. her math test
B. answering questions
C. having friends
D. her teachers

10) When does Tracey seem to be brave?
A. when she cannot eat
B. when she feels better
C. when she holds her dad's hand
D. when she walks up the steps to the school

11) What is Tracey's new school like?
A. big
B. dirty
C. loud
D. small

12) How do the children in Tracey's class seem?
A. kind
B. smart
C. funny
D. different

items.title: Writing Task - Who are you? - Summer Camp

items.content:
In this section you can find the first Writing Task we're going to do together. If you've never had English before or if you want to begin with an easy task (een makkelijke taak) you can do task 1. When you're up for a challenge (een uitdaging) you can do writing task 2. If you finish early, start working on the other task too.

You can find the writing tasks below or you can open the PDF document to see which assignments we're going to do.

Task/option 1 - 'Who are you?'
You're going to write down words that symbolise you! Start by writing your name in the
middle of the square (vierkant). Then you're going to write down words that remind
(doen denken aan/herinneren aan) us of you. You can look up the meaning of words in
your dictionary. You can tell us something about your family, hobbies, favourite food,
favourite colour, best music, best holiday etc. You can find an example (voorbeeld) below. Use every word you write down to make a sentence. Use at least 5 words and make 5 sentences.

Task/option 2 - 'Summer Camp'
Read the text 'Summer Camp' below. Then try to finish the story with your own writing. We're going to write the ending in English. Don't use Google translate to form sentences. Write the story in your own words!

'Summer Camp'

Today was my first day at summer camp! I had a lot of fun. I had to wake up very early. My dad dropped me off at the park and I met my counsellor (begeleider). Her name was Jamie. There were nine other people in my group.

The first thing that we did was go on a nature hike. The hike was long. We walked through the entire park. I saw two squirrels and a rabbit. I was afraid that I was going to see a snake. It was hot and I got a lot of bug bites.

After the hike, we had arts and crafts (knutselen). I made a bookmark to take home with me. I coloured it blue and used a lot of glitter. After arts and crafts, we played my favourite game!

… continue writing from here
